<br>
This, obviously, doesn't become a viable tactic till you get ToT at 51, and probably not until you get the resist falloff at 55.  Probably want C2 too since you'll get little chance to med.  So it'll be a while till I get to experiment with this, but it might be fun to try out some time around there.  Do you find you go through more Periodots doing this, or do you even bother to Rune yourself?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Furthermore, have you tried pulling with Tash or a debuff to keep the aggro spread down?  I've heard the associative aggro range is significantly smaller if you use a non-damage type spell to pull. <p><center><b>51st Tier'Dal Illusionist</b><BR><img src=http://home.netcom.com/~awachs/Sig-Final.JPG> <BR>
(We shall flow a river unto thee, and teeming with souls shall it ever be.)</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uakbarbelakesh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Akbar BelAkesh</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(10/16/01 12:43:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Enchanters as pullers</span><hr size=1> I use a variety of spells to pull <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  Mostly I'll use tash.  Fast cast, low mana, and incredible range.  Not to mention it has this nice side effect of increasing your chance to mez.<br>
<br>
If I'm the slower of the group and I have the spell up sometimes I'll use that.  If I'm low on mana and it's a caster I'm pulling I'll sometimes even use ToT to pull lol.  I never use damage spells to pull. High mana, slow cast rate... I usually want to get in and get out heh.  <br>
<br>
I definitly wouldn't try this unless you know that you have a low resist rate on stuns and mezzes from your normal enchanterly duties. <br>
<br>
Umm Peridots..  Nope, I rarely used Peridots for Rune while pulling.  Before Bedlam I would keep berserker str on me.  Then use tash to pull from a long distance or Stun to aggro if I was right up close.  The first time I get hit, I stop/stun, and keep running.  Most of the time that was enough to keep them off me while I ran back to the group.<br>
<br>
Another GREAT advantage of pulling yourself is that you always know how many mobs you can handle so overpulling is greatly reduced.  Also, you already have the incoming mob targeted... targeting is one of the hardest parts about playing an enchanter lol... so it becomes trivial to mez them once in camp regardless of where they run.<br>
<br>
